    • Constructor Detail

      • Region

        Region(java.lang.String zoneName,
       java.lang.String worldName,
       int minX,
       int minY,
       int minZ,
       int maxX,
       int maxY,
       int maxZ)
        A general constructor, used primarily for regeneration of the regions from databases.
        Parameters:
        zoneName - The name of the zone.
        worldName - The name of the world the zone is in. If worldName points to a non-existent world, world will be null but worldName will be what the world was.
        minX - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's X location.
        minY - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's Y location.
        minZ - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's Z location.
        maxX - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's X location.
        maxY - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's Y location.
        maxZ - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's Z location.

      • Region

        public Region(java.lang.String zoneName,
              java.lang.String worldName,
              org.bukkit.Location minLoc,
              org.bukkit.Location maxLoc)
        The same style of constructor as Region(String zoneName, String worldName, int minX, int minY, int minZ, int maxX, int maxY, int maxZ), but with the coordinates represented by Location objects that include the world.
        Parameters:
        zoneName - The name of the zone.
        worldName - The name of the world the zone is in. If worldName points to a non-existent world, world will be null but worldName will be what the world was.
        minLoc - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point.
        maxLoc - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point.

      • Region

        public Region(java.lang.String zoneName,
              java.lang.String worldName,
              org.bukkit.World world,
              org.bukkit.Location minLoc,
              org.bukkit.Location maxLoc)
        Same style of constructor as Region(String zoneName, String worldName, Location minLoc, Location maxLoc), but with the World reference explicitly made.
        Parameters:
        zoneName - The name of the zone.
        worldName - The name of the world the zone is in. If worldName points to a non-existent world, world will be null but worldName will be what the world was.
        world - An explicit reference to the world the region is in.
        minLoc - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point.
        maxLoc - The Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point.
